    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>Safety Feature Description</title>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Purpose</title>
          <para>The firewall layer at Frame C0 protects the pressurized fuselage from heat and electromagnetic interference generated by active sensors in the radome bay.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Construction</title>
          <para>The firewall consists of a titanium foil barrier, ceramic insulation, and an EMI shielding mesh. It is mounted between the BH-STA350 bulkhead and the radome interface structure.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Integration</title>
          <para>The firewall is partially embedded into Frame C0 and interfaces with the bulkhead and fastener pattern. It allows sensor cabling to pass through shielded conduits while maintaining thermal isolation.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Compliance</title>
          <para>The firewall meets CS-25.867 for fire protection and DO-160G Sections 20 and 23 for electromagnetic and thermal shielding. It is validated under the FIREWALL_COMPLIANT badge.</para>
        </levelledPara>

      </levelledPara>
    </description>
